-- Turkey's Yapi Kredi to issue lira-denominated bonds worth up to 10 bln lira
-- By Ece Toksabay
-- Thu Jul 24, 2014 10:23AM EDT
-- None



ISTANBUL, July 24 (Reuters) - Turkey's Yapi Kredi Bank <YKBNK.IS> said on Thursday it mandated its headquarters to issue lira-denominated bonds worth up to 10 billion lira ($4.8 billion).

The bank said in the statement to the Istanbul stock exchange that the bonds would be of varying maturities.